{"title_page": "Madonna and Child with St Michael and St Bernardino", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{short description|1476 triptych by Neroccio di Bartolomeo de' Landi}}\n[[File:Neroccio_di_bartolomeo_landi,_madonna_col_bambino_e_santi,_1476.JPG|thumb|350px]]\n'''''Madonna and Child with St Michael and St Bernardino''''' is a 1476 tempera and gold on panel [[triptych]] by [[Neroccio di Bartolomeo de' Landi]], now in the [[Pinacoteca Nazionale (Siena)|Pinacoteca Nazionale]] in Siena.<ref>[[Gertrude Coor]], ''Neroccio de' Landi 1447-1500'', Princeton, New Jersey, Princeton University Press, 1961, 235 p., 30 x 23 cm.</ref> To the left is [[St Michael]], whilst to the right is [[Bernardino of Siena]].<ref>{{in lang|fr}} Giulietta Chelazzi Dini, Alessandro Angelini and Bernardina Sani (translated into French by Corinne Paul Ma\u00efer and Ma\u00efa Rosenberger), ''Les peintres de Sienne'', Paris, Imprimerie nationale \u00e9ditions, 1997, 471 p., 29,5 x 35 cm ({{ISBN|2-7433-0237-2}}), p. 299-301.</ref><ref>{{in lang|fr}} Daniel Arasse (preface by Roland Recht), Saint Bernardin de Sienne.Entre d\u00e9votion et culture : fonctions de l'image religieuse au xve si\u00e8cle, Paris, Hazan, 2014, 304 p., 14 x 21 cm ({{ISBN|978-2-7541-0255-1}})</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:1476 paintings]]\n[[Category:Paintings of the Madonna and Child]]\n[[Category:Paintings depicting St Michael]]\n[[Category:Paintings of St Bernardino of Siena]]\n[[Category:Paintings in the Pinacoteca Nazionale (Siena)]]\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{short description|1476 triptych by Neroccio di Bartolomeo de' Landi}}\n[[File:Neroccio_di_bartolomeo_landi,_madonna_col_bambino_e_santi,_1476.JPG|thumb|350px]]\n'''''Madonna and Child with St Michael and St Bernardino''''' is a 1476 tempera and gold on panel [[triptych]] by [[Neroccio di Bartolomeo de' Landi]], now in the [[Pinacoteca Nazionale (Siena)|Pinacoteca Nazionale]] in Siena.<ref>Gertrude Coor, Neroccio de' Landi 1447-1500, Princeton, New Jersey, Princeton University Press, 1961, 235 p., 30 x 23 cm.</ref> To the left is [[St Michael]], whilst to the right is [[Bernardino of Siena]].<ref>{{in lang|fr}} Giulietta Chelazzi Dini, Alessandro Angelini and Bernardina Sani (translated into French by Corinne Paul Ma\u00efer and Ma\u00efa Rosenberger), ''Les peintres de Sienne'', Paris, Imprimerie nationale \u00e9ditions, 1997, 471 p., 29,5 x 35 cm ({{ISBN|2-7433-0237-2}}), p. 299-301.</ref><ref>{{in lang|fr}} Daniel Arasse (preface by Roland Recht), Saint Bernardin de Sienne.Entre d\u00e9votion et culture : fonctions de l'image religieuse au xve si\u00e8cle, Paris, Hazan, 2014, 304 p., 14 x 21 cm ({{ISBN|978-2-7541-0255-1}})</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:1476 paintings]]\n[[Category:Paintings of the Madonna and Child]]\n[[Category:Paintings depicting St Michael]]\n[[Category:Paintings of St Bernardino of Siena]]\n[[Category:Paintings in the Pinacoteca Nazionale (Siena)]]\n", "name_user": "Dsp13", "label": "safe", "comment": "wlink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madonna_and_Child_with_St_Michael_and_St_Bernardino"}
